HEADWORD: Tolsester
<hw>Tol"ses*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>tolsestrum</ets>. Cf. <er>Toll</er> a tax.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>A toll or tribute of a sextary of ale, paid to the lords
of some manors by their tenants, for liberty to brew and sell ale.</def>
<rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

